@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
    Layout = "_Layout";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>GLMS Core Prototype respects privacy and applies data-minimization principles to every feature of the application. When you create clients, contracts, and service requests, the system stores only the information required to perform business operations, such as client contact details, contract dates, service levels, and request descriptions. Uploaded signed agreements are treated as sensitive business documents and are stored on the server in a restricted folder, with access only through authenticated application routes. We log basic operational events, such as contract updates or service request submissions, to support auditability and troubleshooting, but these logs do not include sensitive personal data beyond what is necessary to identify the affected record. Currency conversion requests are performed through a third‑party exchange‑rate service to compute local costs; these requests send only the currency base and target needed for conversion and do not transmit client data. We retain data for as long as required to support active agreements and compliance needs, and we limit access to authorized users based on their role. If you need to correct or remove information, you can do so through the relevant edit or delete actions in the application, ensuring that updates are reflected in reports and operational screens without delay.</p>

<p>Security controls are applied across the application lifecycle to protect data in transit and at rest. All traffic is served over HTTPS, and files are validated to ensure only PDF documents are accepted for signed agreements. The system enforces business rules to prevent the creation of service requests on contracts that are expired or on hold, and it validates inputs before changes are persisted. We use industry‑standard frameworks and database protections to guard against unauthorized access, and we regularly monitor for errors and unusual activity. When you use the application, you may see system‑generated identifiers for clients, contracts, and service requests; these identifiers are internal to the system and are not used to profile users. We do not sell or share personal information with third parties, and any integrations are limited to the minimum scope required for functionality. By continuing to use the system, you acknowledge this privacy policy and agree to the handling of information as described, with the assurance that the platform is designed to keep your data secure, accurate, and available only to those who need it for legitimate business purposes.</p>
